techmeme.title: Meta, Spotify, and Match launch the Coalition for a Competitive Mobile Experience, a lobbying coalition to take on Apple and Google over user age verification (Emily Birnbaum/Bloomberg)
Kintsugi, which uses AI to help companies automate their sales tax compliance, raised $18M at a $150M post-money valuation, up from $80M in November 2024 (Jagmeet Singh/TechCrunch)
Grindr rolls out A-List, powered by Claude Sonnet 3.7 and Amazon Bedrock, to curate "meaningful past connections, high-potential matches" and chat summaries (Natalie Lung/Bloomberg)
AI legal analysis startup Supio, which focuses on personal injury law across 114+ case types, raised $60M led by Sapphire, taking its total funding to $91M (Kyle Wiggers/TechCrunch)
Rogo, which offers an AI chatbot that replicates an investment banker, raised a $50M Series B led by Thrive at a $350M valuation, after raising $18.5M in 2024 (Financial Times)
